In the previous text, the speaker provides a detailed explanation about how ChatGPT, a language model based on the Transformer architecture, works. He explains that the model takes a sequence of text or characters and predicts the next character or word based on the previously mentioned ones. This is trained by modeling the sequence of characters in a given text, in this case, a one megabyte file consisting of all of Shakespeare's works. The speaker is making a point that understanding how ChatGPT works is an important part of understanding more advanced language models.